exporting%20the%20guns%20to%20Soviet-friendly%20countries%20like%20Vietnam%20and%20China%20and%20is%20thought%20to%20have%20distributed%20away%20its%20entire%20arsenal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20gun%20has%20reappeared%20in%20Russian%20hands%20in%20Donetsk%2C%20leading%20Ukrainian%20media%20to%20discuss%20the%20possibility%20that%20it%20was%20imported%20from%20a%20country%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-hit-russian-arsenal-storing-north-korean-weapons-glide-bombs-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENorth%20Korea%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20also%20known%20to%20stockpile%20the%20D-74.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20no%20secret%20that%20Russia%20has%20significant%20struggles%20with%20both%20material%20and%20manpower%2C%26quot%3B%20US%20Marine%20Corps%20Ret.%20Lt.%20Col.%20Michael%20Purcell%2C%20who%20teaches%20classes%20on%20Russia%20and%20International%20Security%20at%20George%20Washington%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20it%20is%20safe%20to%20assume%20that%20these%20systems%2C%20or%20at%20least%20the%20ammunition%2C%20are%20coming%20from%20the%20DPRK.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20publicizing%20to%20the%20world%20that%20it's%20importing%20and%20using%20the%20D-74%20would%20also%20fit%20with%20its%20war%20strategy%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRussia%20has%20not%20been%20shy%20about%20strengthening%20and%20promoting%20its%20defense%20ties%20with%20the%20DPRK%2C%26quot%3B%20Purcell%20said.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20same%20way%20that%20the%20Putin%20regime%20has%20always%20sought%20support%20and%20approval%20from%20marginalized%20states%20regardless%20of%20the%20legitimacy%20of%20the%20government.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222560%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20D-74%20fires%20its%20ammunition%20from%20an%20entrenched%20position.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F670ca30fa703186492818d64%3Fformat%3Djpeg%