0about%2024-25%20years%20old%2C%20she%20learnt%20about%20endometriosis%20from%20a%20friend.%20A%20deep%20research%20into%20the%20disease%20led%20to%20a%20strong%20belief%20that%20she%20indeed%20had%20endometriosis.%20All%20this%20while%2C%20she%20continued%20visiting%20doctors%2C%20hoping%20that%20they%20would%20find%20a%20solution%20for%20her%20pain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20time%20a%20doctor%20took%20her%20seriously%2C%20she%20says%2C%20was%20when%20her%20partner%20accompanied%20her%20and%20stressed%20that%20the%20pain%20she%20experienced%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20normal.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20insisted%20on%20further%20tests%20and%20the%20doctor%20agreed%20to%20take%20an%20MRI.%20I%20was%20undermined%20all%20these%20years%20despite%20knowing%20my%20body%20the%20best.%20They%20just%20had%20to%20listen%20to%20me%3B%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20that%20difficult%20right%3F%E2%80%9D%20she%20laments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20MRI%20confirmed%20Sneha%E2%80%99s%20suspicions%20%E2%80%94%20she%20had%20endometriosis.%20%E2%80%9CI%20cried%20that%20day.%20I%20felt%20robbed%20of%20so%20many%20life%20experiences.%20I%20wish%20they%20had%20just%20listened%20to%20me%20when%20I%20told%20them%20that%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20normal%20period%20pain%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202021%2C%20she%20underwent%20surgery%20to%20check%20her%20endometrial%20tissue.%20The%20doctor%20put%20her%20on%20a%20hormone%20treatment%3B%20this%20didn%E2%80%99t%20work%20for%20her%2C%20leading%20to%20further%20anxiety.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20closed%20me%20up%20and%20said%20that%20the%20tissue%20didn%E2%80%99t%20warrant%20so%20much%20pain.%20It%20messed%20with%20my%20emotional%20and%20mental%20state%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sneha%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnhappy%20with%20the%20treatment%20and%20now%20aware%20and%20educated%20about%20the%20conditi