ed%2C%20Devleena%20underwent%20both%20a%20CT%20and%20MRI%20scan%2C%20which%20revealed%20a%20large%20cyst%20measuring%20around%20nine%20centimetres.%20This%20discovery%20led%20to%20another%20surgery.%20Not%20wanting%20to%20take%20any%20chances%2C%20the%20procedure%20was%20performed%20in%20Delhi%20under%20the%20supervision%20of%20a%20trusted%20colleague%20of%20her%20in-laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhat%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20a%20one-hour%20surgery%20extended%20to%20over%20five%20hours%20due%20to%20the%20liquid%20spreading%20across%20my%20stomach%20and%20digestive%20system.%20They%20also%20had%20to%20remove%20my%20ovary%2C%E2%80%9D%20shares%20Devleena.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnderstanding%20the%20full%20situation%20and%20prioritising%20her%20health%2C%20Devleena%E2%80%99s%20mother-in-law%20urged%20the%20doctors%20to%20remove%20the%20ovary%20during%20the%20surgery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20most%20cases%2C%20especially%20with%20women%20of%20childbearing%20age%2C%20doctors%20usually%20try%20to%20save%20the%20ovary%2C%20but%20that%20can%20lead%20to%20further%20complications%20and%20more%20surgeries.%20I%20come%20from%20a%20very%20progressive%20family%20but%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20if%20most%20people%20will%20take%20that%20stand.%20I%20know%20of%20friends%20who%20weren%E2%80%99t%20even%20asked%20if%20they%20wanted%20to%20have%20a%20child.%20Doctors%20decided%20for%20them%20and%20saved%20the%20ovary.%20They%20had%20to%20undergo%20another%20surgery%20later%2C%E2%80%9D%20Devleena%20shares.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F369525%2Frama-world-mental-health-anxiety-disorder-slow-down-hustle-culture-journalist-breaking-news%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWomen%E2%80%99s%20agency%20and%20their%20wishes%3C%2Fa%3E%20aren%E2%80%99t%20taken%20into%20account%2C%20she%20rues.%20%E2%80%9CMost%20doctors%20advise%20you%20to%20have%20children%20as%20it%20might%20sort%20out%20some%20issues%20according%20to%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESneha%20also%20chimes%20in.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20just%2025%20and%20not%20married.%20The%20doctor%20suggested%20that%20I%20should%20think%20of%20having%20a%20child%20soon.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20women%20have%20finally%20found%20solutions%20to%20their%20pain%20after%20years%20of%20struggles.%20Speaking%20to%20many%20other%20women%20in%20the%20same%20boat%2C%20they%20say%20that%20the%20consensus%20remains%20the%20same%20%E2%80%94%20their%20pain%20is%20not%20taken%20seriously.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20level%20of%20pain%20is%20not%20normal.%20It%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20have%20the%20information%20to%20understand%20what%20your%20body%20is%20going%20through.%20Just%20knowing%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20in%20my%20head%20was%20hugely%20empowering%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Devleena.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhy%20is%20a%20pain%20like%20this%20normalised%3F%E2%80%9D%20asks%20Sneha.%20%E2%80%9CPain%20is%20not%20a%20normal%20physiological%20process.%20Pain%20is%20not%20part%20of%20being%20a%20woman.%20This%20whole%20%E2%80%98women%20need%20to%20endure%20pain%E2%80%99%20mentality%20needs%20to%20stop.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20build%20a%20%23BetterIndiaForWomen%2C%20both%20women%20assert%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20time%20medical%20professionals%20started%20listening%20to%20women.%20It%E2%80%99s%20also%20time%20women%20start%20taking%20their%20health%20seriously.%20%E2%80%9CJust%20listen%20and%20indulge%20women%20who%20come%20seeking%20help%20from%20you.%20Hear%20us%20out.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20in%20our%20head%2C%E2%80%9D%20reiterates%20Sneha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20your%20pain%20is%20bad%20and%20not%20something%20you%E2%80%99ve%20experienced%20before%2C%20go%20to%20a%20doctor.%20Find%20one%20who%20listens%20to%20you%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20give%20up.%20Start%20taking%20care%20of%20yourself%20and%20give%20priority%20to%20your%20own%20health%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1728564604000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D369628%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Devleena%20Chatterjee%20and%20Sneha%20Khedkar%20share%20their%20stories%20of%20living%20with%20debilitating%20pain%20every%20month.%20Doctors%20sent%20them%20home%20with%20painkillers%20saying%20that%20they%20had%20a%20lower%20tolerance%20for%20pain.%20Here%E2%80%99s%20how%20they%20finally%20got%20an%20answer%20through%20an%20endometriosis%20diagnosis.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Sowmya%20Mani%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F369628%2Fendometriosis-gynaecologists-womens-health-pain-periods-menstrual-cramps-devleena-chatterjee-sneha-khedkar%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Breaking%20News%20to%20Breaking%20Point%3A%20How%20a%20Journalist%20Uncovered%20an%20Anxiety%20Disorder%20Through%20Ear%20Pain%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Representational%20Image%20above%20courtesy%20Shutterstock%3C%2Fem%3E)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20was%20a%20constant%20feeling%20of%20darkness%20inside%20and%20outside%20me%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Rama.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20early%202024%2C%20Rama%20started%20experiencing%20pain%20in%20her%20ears%2C%20a%20constant%20sensation%20of%20discomfort%20that%20she%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20overlook.%20This%20kicked%20off%20a%20series%20of%20visits%20to%20Ear%2C%20Nose%2C%20and%20Throat%20(ENT)%20specialists.%20Even%20after%20surgery%2C%20she%20had%20a%20gnawing%20feeling%20that%20something%20was%20still%20wrong%2C%20which%20led%20her%20to%20continue%20visiting%20doctors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20time%2C%20the%20doctors%20assured%20her%20that%20there%20was%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20her%20ears.%20She%20persisted%20in%20seeking%20answers%2C%20visiting%20multiple%20doctors%2C%20hoping%20for%20a%20solution.%20Eventually%2C%20a%20doctor%20suggested%20she%20consult%20a%20psychiatrist%2C%20as%20the%20issue%20might%20be%20related%20to%20anxiety.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20journalist%20with%20over%2019%20years%20of%20experience%2C%20Rama%20visited%20a%20psychiatrist%20on%20her%20first%20day%20at%20a%20new%20job.%20There%2C%20she%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F331893%2Fmental-health-care-therapy-counselling-affordable-startups-india-online%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egeneralised%20anxiety%20disorder%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20mental%20health%20condition%20characterised%20by%20excessive%20fear%20and%20worry%20about%20everyday%20activities%20and%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-quote%20wp-block-quote-is-layout-flow%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EShocked%20by%20the%20diagnosis%2C%20Rama%2C%2044%2C%20found%20solace%20in%20her%20psychiatrist%E2%80%99s%20words%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20can%20pull%20you%20out%20of%20this.%20If%20you%20are%20willing%20to%20help%20me%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20help%20you.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20statement%20made%20a%20world%20of%20difference%20as%20Rama%20finally%20understood%20the%20cause%20of%20her%20persistent%20worries%2C%20sleepless%20nights%2C%20and%20anxiety%20about%20the%20future%20over%20the%20past%20six%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20her%20story%20and%20how%20it%20took%20physical%20pain%20to%20diagnose%20her%20mental%20struggles%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98I%20was%20gripped%20by%20a%20fear%20of%20the%20future%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBorn%20and%20raised%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20Rama%20moved%20to%20Chennai%20in%202018%20for%20a%20job.%20Adjusting%20to%20a%20new%20city%2C%20culture%2C%20people%2C%20and%20workplace%20was%20challenging%20for%20her%2C%20especially%20while%20living%20alone.%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20not%20easy%20coming%20home%20to%20an%20empty%20apartment%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20admits%20candidly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20hindsight%2C%20she%20realised%20that%20living%20alone%20triggered%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F173434%2Fkerala-free-mental-health-care-doctor-inspiring-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseveral%20episodes%20of%20anxiety.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Deeply%20ambitious%2C%20she%20had%20charted%20out%20a%20path%20for%20herself%2C%20and%20when%20things%20didn%E2%80%99t%20go%20as%20planned%2C%20they%20affected%20her%20deeply.%20%E2%80%9CI%20didn%E2%80%99t%20even%20realise%20I%20was%20anxious%20or%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20see%20a%20doctor.%20I%20would%20have%20palpitations%20but%20somehow%20powered%20through%20as%20I%20had%20work%20to%20finish%2C%E2%80%9D%20Rama%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorking%20in%20a%20fast-paced%20setup%20where%20breaking%20news%20took%20priority%20and%20daily%20newspaper%20editions%20had%20to%20be%20sent%20out%2C%20she%20often%20neglected%20her%20own%20mental%20health.%20%E2%80%9CI%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20time%20to%20slow%20down%2C%20and%20honestly%2C%20I%20never%20understood%20its%20importance.%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20speak%20up%20for%20what%20I%20needed.%20Taking%20a%20break%20or%20slowing%20down%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20you%E2%80%99re%20doing%20less%2C%20as%20I%20now%20realise%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2Ftips-to-cope-with-anxiety-1728485507.png%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.c